altigaL2tpStatsMibModule.name: altigaL2tpStatsMibModule
altigaL2tpStatsMibModule.contactinfo: Cisco Systems 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-cvpn3000@cisco.com
altigaL2tpStatsMibModule.description: The Altiga L2TP Statistics MIB models counters and objects that are of management interest for L2TP tunnels. Acronyms The following acronyms are used in this document: AVP: Attribute/Value Pair CLID: Calling Line ID DNIS: Dialed Number Identification Service L2TP: Layer 2 Tunnel Protocol LAC: L2TP Access Concentrator LNS: L2TP Network Server MIB: Management Information Base RWS: Receive Window Size

alL2tpStatsLocalProtVers.name: alL2tpStatsLocalProtVers
alL2tpStatsLocalProtVers.description: This object describes the protocol version and revision of the local implementation. The first octet contains the protocol version. The second octet contains the protocol revision.

alL2tpStatsVendorName.name: alL2tpStatsVendorName
alL2tpStatsVendorName.description: This object identifies the Vendor name.

alL2tpStatsFirmwareRev.name: alL2tpStatsFirmwareRev
alL2tpStatsFirmwareRev.description: This object defines the firmware revision.

alL2tpStatsTotalTunnels.name: alL2tpStatsTotalTunnels
alL2tpStatsTotalTunnels.description: This object returns the total number of tunnels that have successfully reached the established state.

alL2tpStatsFailedTunnels.name: alL2tpStatsFailedTunnels
alL2tpStatsFailedTunnels.description: This object returns the number of tunnels that failed to reach the established state.

alL2tpStatsFailedAuthentications.name: alL2tpStatsFailedAuthentications
alL2tpStatsFailedAuthentications.description: This object returns the number of failed tunnel connection attempts because the tunnel peer failed authentication.

alL2tpStatsActiveTunnels.name: alL2tpStatsActiveTunnels
alL2tpStatsActiveTunnels.description: This object returns the number of tunnels that are currently active.

alL2tpStatsMaxTunnels.name: alL2tpStatsMaxTunnels
alL2tpStatsMaxTunnels.description: The maximum number of simultaneously active L2TP tunnels since the system was booted.

alL2tpStatsTotalSessions.name: alL2tpStatsTotalSessions
alL2tpStatsTotalSessions.description: This object returns the total number of sessions that have successfully reached the established state.

alL2tpStatsFailedSessions.name: alL2tpStatsFailedSessions
alL2tpStatsFailedSessions.description: This object returns the number of sessions that failed to reach the established state for this tunnel domain.

alL2tpStatsActiveSessions.name: alL2tpStatsActiveSessions
alL2tpStatsActiveSessions.description: This object returns the number of sessions that are currently active.

alL2tpStatsMaxSessions.name: alL2tpStatsMaxSessions
alL2tpStatsMaxSessions.description: The maximum number of simultaneously active L2TP sessions since the system was booted.

alL2tpStatsControlRecvOctets.name: alL2tpStatsControlRecvOctets
alL2tpStatsControlRecvOctets.description: This object returns the number of control channel octets received.

alL2tpStatsControlRecvPackets.name: alL2tpStatsControlRecvPackets
alL2tpStatsControlRecvPackets.description: This object returns the number of control packets received.

alL2tpStatsControlRecvDiscards.name: alL2tpStatsControlRecvDiscards
alL2tpStatsControlRecvDiscards.description: This object returns the number of control packets received that were discarded.

alL2tpStatsControlSendOctets.name: alL2tpStatsControlSendOctets
alL2tpStatsControlSendOctets.description: This object returns the number of control channel octets that were transmitted to tunnel endpoints.

alL2tpStatsControlSendPackets.name: alL2tpStatsControlSendPackets
alL2tpStatsControlSendPackets.description: This object returns the number of control packets that were transmitted to tunnel endpoints.

alL2tpStatsPayloadRecvOctets.name: alL2tpStatsPayloadRecvOctets
alL2tpStatsPayloadRecvOctets.description: This object returns the number of payload channel octets that were received.

alL2tpStatsPayloadRecvPackets.name: alL2tpStatsPayloadRecvPackets
alL2tpStatsPayloadRecvPackets.description: This object returns the number of payload packets that were received.

alL2tpStatsPayloadRecvDiscards.name: alL2tpStatsPayloadRecvDiscards
alL2tpStatsPayloadRecvDiscards.description: This object returns the number of received payload packets that were discarded.

alL2tpStatsPayloadSendOctets.name: alL2tpStatsPayloadSendOctets
alL2tpStatsPayloadSendOctets.description: This object returns the number of payload channel octets that were transmitted to tunnel peers.

alL2tpStatsPayloadSendPackets.name: alL2tpStatsPayloadSendPackets
alL2tpStatsPayloadSendPackets.description: This object returns the number of payload packets that were transmitted to tunnel peers.

alL2tpStatsTunnelTable.name: alL2tpStatsTunnelTable
alL2tpStatsTunnelTable.description: The L2TP tunnel status and statistics table.

alL2tpStatsTunnelRowStatus.name: alL2tpStatsTunnelRowStatus
alL2tpStatsTunnelRowStatus.description: The status of this row. Used to terminate the tunnel, cannot be used to create a tunnel.

alL2tpStatsTunnelPeerIpAddr.name: alL2tpStatsTunnelPeerIpAddr
alL2tpStatsTunnelPeerIpAddr.description: The peer's IP address for this tunnel.

alL2tpStatsTunnelLocalTID.name: alL2tpStatsTunnelLocalTID
alL2tpStatsTunnelLocalTID.description: This object contains the local tunnel Identifier.

alL2tpStatsTunnelRemoteTID.name: alL2tpStatsTunnelRemoteTID
alL2tpStatsTunnelRemoteTID.description: This object contains the remote tunnel Identifier.

alL2tpStatsTunnelState.name: alL2tpStatsTunnelState
alL2tpStatsTunnelState.description: This field contains the current state of the control tunnel.

alL2tpStatsTunnelInitiated.name: alL2tpStatsTunnelInitiated
alL2tpStatsTunnelInitiated.description: This object indicates whether the tunnel was initiated locally or by the remote tunnel peer.

alL2tpStatsTunnelRemoteHostName.name: alL2tpStatsTunnelRemoteHostName
alL2tpStatsTunnelRemoteHostName.description: This object contains the host name as discovered during the tunnel establishment phase (via the Host Name AVP) of the L2TP peer. If the tunnel is idle this object should maintain its value from the last time it was connected.

alL2tpStatsTunnelRemoteVendorName.name: alL2tpStatsTunnelRemoteVendorName
alL2tpStatsTunnelRemoteVendorName.description: This object identifies the vendor name of the peer's L2TP implementation. If the tunnel is idle this object should maintain its value from the last time it was connected.

alL2tpStatsTunnelRemoteFirmwareRevision.name: alL2tpStatsTunnelRemoteFirmwareRevision
alL2tpStatsTunnelRemoteFirmwareRevision.description: This object contains the tunnel peer's firmware revision number. If the tunnel is idle this object should maintain its value from the last time it was connected.

alL2tpStatsTunnelRemoteProtocolVersion.name: alL2tpStatsTunnelRemoteProtocolVersion
alL2tpStatsTunnelRemoteProtocolVersion.description: This object describes the protocol version and revision of the tunnel peers implementation. The first octet contains the protocol version. The second octet contains the protocol revision.

alL2tpStatsTunnelInitialRemoteRWS.name: alL2tpStatsTunnelInitialRemoteRWS
alL2tpStatsTunnelInitialRemoteRWS.description: This object contains the initial remote peer's receive window size as indicated by the tunnel peer (in the RWS AVP) during the tunnel establishment phase. If the tunnel is idle this object should maintain its value from the last time it was connected.

alL2tpStatsTunnelBearerCapabilities.name: alL2tpStatsTunnelBearerCapabilities
alL2tpStatsTunnelBearerCapabilities.description: This object describes the Bearer Capabilities of the tunnel peer. If the tunnel is idle this object should maintain its value from the last time it was connected.

alL2tpStatsTunnelFramingCapabilities.name: alL2tpStatsTunnelFramingCapabilities
alL2tpStatsTunnelFramingCapabilities.description: This object describes the Framing Capabilities of the tunnel peer. If the tunnel is idle this object should maintain its value from the last time it was connected.

alL2tpStatsTunnelControlRecvPackets.name: alL2tpStatsTunnelControlRecvPackets
alL2tpStatsTunnelControlRecvPackets.description: This object contains the number of control packets received on the tunnel.

alL2tpStatsTunnelControlRecvDiscards.name: alL2tpStatsTunnelControlRecvDiscards
alL2tpStatsTunnelControlRecvDiscards.description: This object returns the number of received payload packets that were discarded.

alL2tpStatsTunnelControlRecvZLB.name: alL2tpStatsTunnelControlRecvZLB
alL2tpStatsTunnelControlRecvZLB.description: This object returns a count of the number of Zero Length Body control packet acknowledgement packets that were received.

alL2tpStatsTunnelControlOutOfSequence.name: alL2tpStatsTunnelControlOutOfSequence
alL2tpStatsTunnelControlOutOfSequence.description: This object returns a count of the number of control packets that were not received in the correct order (as per the sequence number) on this tunnel.

alL2tpStatsTunnelControlOutOfWindow.name: alL2tpStatsTunnelControlOutOfWindow
alL2tpStatsTunnelControlOutOfWindow.description: This object contains the number of control packets that were received outside of the offered receive window. It is implementation specific as to whether these packets are queued or discarded.

alL2tpStatsTunnelControlSendPackets.name: alL2tpStatsTunnelControlSendPackets
alL2tpStatsTunnelControlSendPackets.description: This object contains the number of control packets that were transmitted to the tunnel peer.

alL2tpStatsTunnelControlSendZLB.name: alL2tpStatsTunnelControlSendZLB
alL2tpStatsTunnelControlSendZLB.description: This object contains the number of Zero Length Body control packets that were transmitted to the tunnel peer.

alL2tpStatsTunnelControlAckTimeouts.name: alL2tpStatsTunnelControlAckTimeouts
alL2tpStatsTunnelControlAckTimeouts.description: This object returns a count of the number of control packet timeouts due to the lack of a timely acknowledgement from the tunnel peer.

alL2tpStatsTunnelCurrentRemoteRWS.name: alL2tpStatsTunnelCurrentRemoteRWS
alL2tpStatsTunnelCurrentRemoteRWS.description: This object contains the current remote receive window size as determined by the local flow control mechanism employed.

alL2tpStatsTunnelSendSeq.name: alL2tpStatsTunnelSendSeq
alL2tpStatsTunnelSendSeq.description: This object contains the next send sequence number for the control channel.

alL2tpStatsTunnelSendSeqAck.name: alL2tpStatsTunnelSendSeqAck
alL2tpStatsTunnelSendSeqAck.description: This object contains the send sequence number that the tunnel peer has acknowledged for the control channel. The flow control state can be determined by subtracting the l2tpTunnelStatsSendSeq from alL2tpStatsTunnelSendSeqAck and comparing this value to l2tpTunnelStatsCurrentRemoteRWS.

alL2tpStatsTunnelRecvSeq.name: alL2tpStatsTunnelRecvSeq
alL2tpStatsTunnelRecvSeq.description: This object contains the next receive sequence number expected to be received on this control channel.

alL2tpStatsTunnelRecvSeqAck.name: alL2tpStatsTunnelRecvSeqAck
alL2tpStatsTunnelRecvSeqAck.description: This object contains the last receive sequence number that was acknowledged back to the tunnel peer for the control channel.

alL2tpStatsTunnelTotalSessions.name: alL2tpStatsTunnelTotalSessions
alL2tpStatsTunnelTotalSessions.description: This object contains the total number of sessions that this tunnel has successfully connected through to its tunnel peer since this tunnel was created.

alL2tpStatsTunnelFailedSessions.name: alL2tpStatsTunnelFailedSessions
alL2tpStatsTunnelFailedSessions.description: This object contains the total number of sessions that were initiated but failed to reach the established phase.

alL2tpStatsTunnelActiveSessions.name: alL2tpStatsTunnelActiveSessions
alL2tpStatsTunnelActiveSessions.description: This object contains the total number of sessions for this tunnel.

alL2tpStatsTunnelLastResultCode.name: alL2tpStatsTunnelLastResultCode
alL2tpStatsTunnelLastResultCode.description: This object contains the last value of the result code as described in the Result Code AVP which caused the tunnel to disconnect.

alL2tpStatsTunnelLastErrorCode.name: alL2tpStatsTunnelLastErrorCode
alL2tpStatsTunnelLastErrorCode.description: This object contains the last value of the error code as described in the Result Code AVP which caused the tunnel to disconnect.

alL2tpStatsTunnelLastErrorMessage.name: alL2tpStatsTunnelLastErrorMessage
alL2tpStatsTunnelLastErrorMessage.description: This object contains the last value of the optional message as described in the Result Code AVP which caused the tunnel to disconnect.

alL2tpStatsSessionTable.name: alL2tpStatsSessionTable
alL2tpStatsSessionTable.description: The L2TP session status and statistics table.

alL2tpStatsSessionEntry.name: alL2tpStatsSessionEntry
alL2tpStatsSessionEntry.description: An L2TP session interface stats entry.

alL2tpStatsSessionRowStatus.name: alL2tpStatsSessionRowStatus
alL2tpStatsSessionRowStatus.description: The status of this row. Used to terminate the session, cannot be used to create a session.

alL2tpStatsSessionIfIndex.name: alL2tpStatsSessionIfIndex
alL2tpStatsSessionIfIndex.description: This value for this object is equal to the value of ifIndex of the Interfaces MIB for session interfaces of type L2TP.

alL2tpStatsSessionTID.name: alL2tpStatsSessionTID
alL2tpStatsSessionTID.description: This object contains the control channel tunnel identifier for this session.

alL2tpStatsSessionLocalCID.name: alL2tpStatsSessionLocalCID
alL2tpStatsSessionLocalCID.description: This object contains the local call identifier for the session.

alL2tpStatsSessionRemoteCID.name: alL2tpStatsSessionRemoteCID
alL2tpStatsSessionRemoteCID.description: This object contains the remote call identifier for the session.

alL2tpStatsSessionUserName.name: alL2tpStatsSessionUserName
alL2tpStatsSessionUserName.description: This object identifies the peer session name on this interface. This is typically the login name of the remote user. If the user name is unknown to the local tunnel peer then this object will contain a null string.

alL2tpStatsSessionState.name: alL2tpStatsSessionState
alL2tpStatsSessionState.description: This object contains the current state of the session.

alL2tpStatsSessionCallType.name: alL2tpStatsSessionCallType
alL2tpStatsSessionCallType.description: This object indicates the type of call and the role this tunnel peer is providing for this session. For example, lacIncoming(1) indicates that this tunnel peer is acting as a LAC and generated a Incoming-Call-Request to the tunnel peer (the LNS). Note that tunnel peers can be both LAC and LNS simultaneously.

alL2tpStatsSessionCallSerialNumber.name: alL2tpStatsSessionCallSerialNumber
alL2tpStatsSessionCallSerialNumber.description: This object contains the serial number that has been assigned to this session.

alL2tpStatsSessionTxConnectSpeed.name: alL2tpStatsSessionTxConnectSpeed
alL2tpStatsSessionTxConnectSpeed.description: This object returns the last known transmit baud rate for this session.

alL2tpStatsSessionRxConnectSpeed.name: alL2tpStatsSessionRxConnectSpeed
alL2tpStatsSessionRxConnectSpeed.description: This object returns the last known receive baud rate for this session.

alL2tpStatsSessionCallBearerType.name: alL2tpStatsSessionCallBearerType
alL2tpStatsSessionCallBearerType.description: This object describes the bearer type of this session.

alL2tpStatsSessionFramingType.name: alL2tpStatsSessionFramingType
alL2tpStatsSessionFramingType.description: This object describes the framing type of this session.

alL2tpStatsSessionPhysChanId.name: alL2tpStatsSessionPhysChanId
alL2tpStatsSessionPhysChanId.description: This object contains the physical channel identifier for the session.

alL2tpStatsSessionDNIS.name: alL2tpStatsSessionDNIS
alL2tpStatsSessionDNIS.description: This object identifies the Dialed Number Information String that the LAC obtained from the network for the session. If no DNIS was provided then a null string will be returned.

alL2tpStatsSessionCLID.name: alL2tpStatsSessionCLID
alL2tpStatsSessionCLID.description: This object identifies the Calling Line ID that the LAC obtained from the network for the session. If no CLID was provided then a null string will be returned.

alL2tpStatsSessionSubAddress.name: alL2tpStatsSessionSubAddress
alL2tpStatsSessionSubAddress.description: This object identifies the Sub Address that the LAC obtained from the network for the session. If no Sub Address was provided then a null string will be returned.

alL2tpStatsSessionPrivateGroupID.name: alL2tpStatsSessionPrivateGroupID
alL2tpStatsSessionPrivateGroupID.description: This object identifies the Private Group Identifier used for this tunneled session. If no Private Group Identifier was provided then a null string will be returned.

alL2tpStatsSessionProxyLcp.name: alL2tpStatsSessionProxyLcp
alL2tpStatsSessionProxyLcp.description: Indicates whether the LAC performed proxy LCP for this session.

alL2tpStatsSessionAuthMethod.name: alL2tpStatsSessionAuthMethod
alL2tpStatsSessionAuthMethod.description: This object contains the proxy authentication method employed by the LAC for the session. If l2tpSessionProxyLcp is false(2) this object should not be interpreted.

alL2tpStatsSessionLocalRWS.name: alL2tpStatsSessionLocalRWS
alL2tpStatsSessionLocalRWS.description: This object returns the local send window size for this session. If the value of the object alL2tpStatsSessionSequencingState is none(1) then this object should not be interpreted.

alL2tpStatsSessionRemoteInitialRWS.name: alL2tpStatsSessionRemoteInitialRWS
alL2tpStatsSessionRemoteInitialRWS.description: This object returns the initial remote send window size for this session. If the value of the object alL2tpStatsSessionSequencingState is none(1) then this object should not be interpreted.

alL2tpStatsSessionRemotePPD.name: alL2tpStatsSessionRemotePPD
alL2tpStatsSessionRemotePPD.description: This object contains the Packet Processing Delay for the session. If the value of the object alL2tpStatsSessionSequencingState is none(1) then this object should not be interpreted.

alL2tpStatsSessionSequencingState.name: alL2tpStatsSessionSequencingState
alL2tpStatsSessionSequencingState.description: This object defines which tunnel peers have requested payload sequencing. The value of both(4) indicates that both peers have requested payload sequencing.

alL2tpStatsSessionRecvOctets.name: alL2tpStatsSessionRecvOctets
alL2tpStatsSessionRecvOctets.description: This object returns the total number payload octets received for this session.

alL2tpStatsSessionRecvPackets.name: alL2tpStatsSessionRecvPackets
alL2tpStatsSessionRecvPackets.description: This object returns the total number of payload packets received for this session.

alL2tpStatsSessionRecvDiscards.name: alL2tpStatsSessionRecvDiscards
alL2tpStatsSessionRecvDiscards.description: This object returns the total number of payload packets received that were discarded for this session.

alL2tpStatsSessionRecvZLB.name: alL2tpStatsSessionRecvZLB
alL2tpStatsSessionRecvZLB.description: This object returns the total number of Zero Length Body acknowlegement payload packets received for this session.

alL2tpStatsSessionOutSequence.name: alL2tpStatsSessionOutSequence
alL2tpStatsSessionOutSequence.description: This object returns the total number of packets received for this session which were received out of sequence.

alL2tpStatsSessionOutOfWindow.name: alL2tpStatsSessionOutOfWindow
alL2tpStatsSessionOutOfWindow.description: This object returns a count of the number of payload packets that were received outside of the expected window for this session.

alL2tpStatsSessionSendOctets.name: alL2tpStatsSessionSendOctets
alL2tpStatsSessionSendOctets.description: This object returns the total number of payload octets transmitted for this session.

alL2tpStatsSessionSendPackets.name: alL2tpStatsSessionSendPackets
alL2tpStatsSessionSendPackets.description: This object returns the total number of payload packets transmitted for this session.

alL2tpStatsSessionSendZLB.name: alL2tpStatsSessionSendZLB
alL2tpStatsSessionSendZLB.description: This object returns the total number of Zero Length Body acknowledgement packets transmitted for this session.

alL2tpStatsSessionAckTimeouts.name: alL2tpStatsSessionAckTimeouts
alL2tpStatsSessionAckTimeouts.description: This object returns the total number of acknowledgement timeouts seen on payload packets for this session.

alL2tpStatsSessionReassemblyTimeouts.name: alL2tpStatsSessionReassemblyTimeouts
alL2tpStatsSessionReassemblyTimeouts.description: This object returns the number of reassembly time outs that have occured for this session.

alL2tpStatsSessionCurrentRemoteRWS.name: alL2tpStatsSessionCurrentRemoteRWS
alL2tpStatsSessionCurrentRemoteRWS.description: This object contains the current remote receive window size as determined by the local flow control mechanism employed.

alL2tpStatsSessionSendSeq.name: alL2tpStatsSessionSendSeq
alL2tpStatsSessionSendSeq.description: This object contains the next send sequence number for for this session.

alL2tpStatsSessionSendSeqAck.name: alL2tpStatsSessionSendSeqAck
alL2tpStatsSessionSendSeqAck.description: This object contains the send sequence number that the tunnel peer has acknowledged for the payload channel. The flow control state can be determined by subtracting the alL2tpStatsSessionSendSeq from alL2tpStatsSessionSendSeqAck and comparing this value to l2tpSesssionStatsCurrentRemoteRWS.

alL2tpStatsSessionSendSeqResets.name: alL2tpStatsSessionSendSeqResets
alL2tpStatsSessionSendSeqResets.description: This object contains the total number of sequence number resets (payload packets with the R-bit set) sent on this session.

alL2tpStatsSessionRecvSeq.name: alL2tpStatsSessionRecvSeq
alL2tpStatsSessionRecvSeq.description: This object contains the next receive sequence number expected to be received on this session.

alL2tpStatsSessionRecvSeqAck.name: alL2tpStatsSessionRecvSeqAck
alL2tpStatsSessionRecvSeqAck.description: This object contains the last receive sequence number that was acknowledged back to the tunnel peer for the session.

alL2tpStatsSessionRecvSeqResets.name: alL2tpStatsSessionRecvSeqResets
alL2tpStatsSessionRecvSeqResets.description: This object contains the total number of sequence number resets (payload packets with the R-bit set) received on this session.

alL2tpStatsSessionTunnelPeerIpAddr.name: alL2tpStatsSessionTunnelPeerIpAddr
alL2tpStatsSessionTunnelPeerIpAddr.description: The peer's IP address for the tunnel to which this session belongs.

altigaL2tpStatsMibCompliance.name: altigaL2tpStatsMibCompliance
altigaL2tpStatsMibCompliance.description: The compliance statement for agents which implement the Altiga L2TP Statistics MIB.

altigaL2tpStatsDepGroup.name: altigaL2tpStatsDepGroup
altigaL2tpStatsDepGroup.description: The deprecated objects for L2TP statistics.
